SIMPLE: unyoke
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unyoke
<hw>Un*yoke"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>yoke</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To loose or free from a yoke.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Like
youthful steers <xex>unyoked</xex>, they take their courses.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To part; to disjoin; to disconnect.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unyoked</ent>⟦br⟧
